The paper presents an approximate distance oracle for a point set, which involves data structures and algorithms for geometric problems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also deals with computational geometry, which falls under cs.CG (Computational Geometry). The paper involves approximation algorithms, which can be categorized under cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The paper also involves information theory, which can be categorized under cs.IT (Information Theory). Finally, the paper involves dynamic data structures, which can be categorized under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
